## Content Schema

Every recipe Markdown file in `src/content/recipes/` must have the following frontmatter, validated by Zod in `src/content/config.ts`:

```ts
{
  title: string;           // Display name of the recipe
  image: string;           // Absolute path from public/, e.g. "/images/recipes/my-recipe.png"
  time: number;            // Prep + cook time in minutes (positive integer)
  rating: number;          // 1вЂ“5 star rating
  ingredients: string[];   // List of ingredients as plain strings
  notes?: string;          // Optional extra notes
}
```

The Markdown body below the frontmatter contains the step-by-step cooking instructions, typically as a numbered list under a `## Instructions` heading.

## Naming Conventions

- **Recipe slugs / filenames**: kebab-case, e.g. `chicken-tikka-masala.md`. The slug drives the URL (`/recipes/chicken-tikka-masala`) and the image filename (`/images/recipes/chicken-tikka-masala.png`).
- **Components**: PascalCase `.astro` files, e.g. `RecipeCard.astro`.
- **Pages**: lowercase kebab-case `.astro` files.
- **CSS classes**: Tailwind utility classes only. Custom classes are minimal and defined in `global.css`.

## Coding Conventions

- All `.astro` files use TypeScript in the frontmatter fence (`---`). Strict types are enforced вЂ” avoid `any`.
- Component props are defined with an `interface Props { ... }` block inside the frontmatter.
- Use Astro's `<slot />` for layout composition.
- Prefer Astro components over framework components (no React/Vue/Svelte installed).
- Images are referenced from `public/` and loaded with `loading="lazy"` and `decoding="async"`.
- Dark mode is class-based (`dark` on `<html>`). Always provide `dark:` variants for colors when adding new UI. The user's preference is persisted to `localStorage`.
- Tailwind `dark:` custom colours used throughout: `dark-bg`, `dark-surface`, `dark-border`, `dark-text`, `dark-text-muted` вЂ” defined in `global.css`.
- The primary accent color is **violet** (`violet-600` / `violet-400` in dark mode).

## Adding a New Recipe

1. Create `src/content/recipes/<slug>.md` with the required frontmatter fields.
2. Add a corresponding image at `public/images/recipes/<slug>.png` (preferred) or `.jpg`.
3. Write the recipe body in Markdown below the frontmatter, using `## Instructions` as the main heading and a numbered list for steps.
4. No other code changes are needed вЂ” the dynamic `[slug].astro` page and recipe listing pick it up automatically.

## Development Commands

```
npm run dev       # Start dev server at http://localhost:4321
npm run build     # Build static output to dist/
npm run preview   # Preview the production build locally
```

## Deployment

- Push to the `main` branch to trigger automatic GitHub Pages deployment via GitHub Actions.
- The site URL is `https://joshuasimon.github.io` (no subdirectory/base path).
- Do not change the `site` value in `astro.config.mjs` without also updating the GitHub Pages configuration.

## Out of Scope (v1)

Do not implement or suggest the following вЂ” they are explicitly deferred to future versions:

- User authentication or OAuth
- A CMS editing UI
- Recipe search or filtering
- Dynamic ratings or user reviews
- A backend or database (e.g. SQLite)
- Comments or social features

## Agent Guidance

- When modifying components, always check for and maintain `dark:` Tailwind variants.
- When adding new pages, extend `BaseLayout.astro` and follow the existing meta/OG tag patterns.
- Do not introduce new npm dependencies without a clear reason вЂ” keep the bundle lean.
- Do not modify `dist/` вЂ” it is a build artifact.
- Do not commit `.DS_Store` or other OS-specific files.
- Prefer editing existing components over creating new abstractions unless the reuse case is clear.
- Recipe instructions may be in German or English вЂ” do not translate existing content.
- Keep accessibility in mind: use semantic HTML, `alt` text on images, and maintain the existing skip-link pattern.